President  Dilma Rousseff  wants
automakers to avoid laying off workers on the first signs of a
serious economic slowdown, Folha de S.Paulo reported, without
saying where it got the information.  Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  will meet representatives of
carmakers next week to make the request, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
